installing node js on linux
nodejs is already preinstalled on every machine.
but it is not the latest version
install nvm node version manage.

follow these steps:

create these files 

touch ~/.bash_profile
touch ~/.bashrc
touch ~/.zshrc
touch ~/.profile

after these files are created in your home directory, then you're ready to download nvm.

go to the nvm repository on github
https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm#installing-and-updating

curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.1/install.sh | bash

how to upgrade nodejs to latest version

use this comand to see all the node versions up to the current version.
including the latest version

next install
nodejs using nvm
 nvm install <the version you want>

